Visualizations

What to look for: Top-right = Elite shooters (high volume + high efficiency). Top-left = Efficient low-volume shooters. Red trendline shows average relationship. Players above the line overperform given their volume.
What to look for: 3PAA (X) rewards total value. 3PES (Y) penalizes volume. Top-right = Elite in both. Above trendline = exceptional efficiency despite volume.
What to look for: Select up to 5 players to compare. Larger shapes = better at that distance. See who excels when guarded vs. wide open. Compare to league average.
What to look for: Greatest single-season 3PT performances (min 82 attempts). Bar shows 3PES relative to #1. Click players to view full profile.
What to look for: Steeper slopes = more value per season. Young players with steep slopes catching veterans. Flat lines = injuries/decline. Hover to identify.
